@kronos  

You're right, sir\_dwar is wrong. Standstill is sacrificed on the RESOLUTION of the triggered ability, not when the ability goes on the stack. Only when the ability that draws you three cards resolves will Standstill cause itself to sacrifice. [Stifle](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stifle), [Trickbind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Trickbind), or [Voidslime](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Voidslime) would counter not only the card draw but also the sacrifice of Standstill.  

Of course, playing any one of those ability counterspells just causes another instance of Standstill's triggered ability to be put on the stack on top of it, so the point is moot.

